				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				When you guys are talking about melees, you are all thinking about monks.<BR>
Fine with me, Monks are way too powerful in my opinion and they really have an easy time leveling and finding groups.<BR>
But they are so tough for one thing : 95% of the monks I know in game are alternate characters of a high level caster, thus they are twinked to the core.<BR>
The reason is quite simple : No main-char melees will ever camp for loots like casters, because they can't.<BR>
The 4 pure casters (wiz, enc, nec, mag) could camp so easily stuffs on their own and make cash that it's not even funny. How many times have I seen just one necro or one magician camping for a FBSS that they will sell to a melee alt of another caster guy.<BR>
Now I ask you : How this may be fair in EverQuest ?<BR>
Next time you see a melee *****ing about casters, it's probably a pure melee player, not twinked, and I think his reasons to complain are legits.<BR>
<BR>
One last thing : Casters DO have an easy time at the end game. Not all the mobs are 100% immune to magical damage. In fact, there are maybe 5% that are immune to it. Don't make such generalizations.<BR>
I do play in a raiding guild and in my experiences, casters ARE the core of the damage-dealing of the raid, not the melee. A lagging caster can still make 100% of its damage output. A lagging melee will be happy to make 50% of his.
				</font>
